H3.text: At 1900 the largest fishing port in the world was. Grimsby

A4.text: By 1900, a tenth of the fish consumed in the United Kingdom was landed there

A5.text: The first true fish dock opened in Grimsby in 1856, and the town became central to the development of the commercial fishing industry
